This paper deals with algorithms for optimization problems on graphical models, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) in the analysis of the algorithm. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of belief propagation, which is a popular technique in the field of signal processing and inference (cs.SI).
